Editors :

Vi : visual display editor.

It will show all lines in black and white colour . It is a older editor it will come by default to the system.

vim : visual display editor improved:-

It will shows all the lines with some colours.It is an upgraded it will come by defaultly to some systems. If we 
we need to install this with package.

It has 3 modes .

1)Command mode :

 whenever we are opeaning any of file by default we will in command mode .
 
some commands in command mode :-

gg - whenever we try to come first line first we use gg.
shift + g = G - It helps to come to end of page.
w - If we want to move word by use w to farward. 5w (It moves 5 words forward) nw ie. nword forward
b - If we want to move word by use b to backward.5b (It moves 5 words backward) nb ie. nword backward
u - to undo the last change.
ctrl+R  - to redo the change
yy - to copy the lines ; 100yy to copy 100 lines. nyy
dd - to delete the lines ; 100dd meand to delete the 100 lines. ndd  to delete n no of lines.
p - to paste the lines below the line.
shift+p - to paste the line above the cursor.
dw - To delete a particular word .
x - To delete a particular character.


/ (or) ? -->To find a word.
:/%s/private/public/g'  To replace word

/ -is used to search the word.

if we want to find how many time the word is occuring press ---n


2)Insert mode:-
 with the help of this we just write what we want to write.

3)Extended command mode:-(ESC) i.e .. (collan mode :)

ESC+ :W ---To save the changes
ESC+ :q ---To quit without saving.
ESC+ :wq ---To save and quit.
ESC+ :wq! ---To save and quit forcefully.
ESC+ :q! --->To quit forcefully without saving.
ESC+ :se nu -->to set the line number to file.


commands :-
--------

Move by characters:
  Ctrl + F     → Move forward (right)
  Ctrl + B     → Move backward (left)

Move by words:
  Alt + F      → Move forward by one word
  Alt + B      → Move backward by one word

Move to line ends:
  Ctrl + A     → Jump to start of line
  Ctrl + E     → Jump to end of line

Delete text:
  Ctrl + D     → Delete character under cursor
  Ctrl + U     → Delete from cursor to start of line
  Ctrl + K     → Delete from cursor to end of line
  Ctrl + W     → Delete previous word
  Alt + D      → Delete next word

Clipboard actions:
  Ctrl + Y     → Paste last deleted text
  Ctrl + _     → Undo last change (sometimes Ctrl + Shift + -)

History & navigation:
  ↑ / ↓        → Browse previous or next commands
  Ctrl + R     → Search command history
  !!           → Repeat last command
  !<text>      → Run last command starting with <text>
  Ctrl + L     → Clear screen (same as 'clear')

Other useful:
  Tab          → Auto-complete command or filename
  Ctrl + C     → Cancel current command
  Ctrl + Z     → Suspend process (use 'fg' to resume)


